        <h3 style="margin-top: 0px;" id="pop_facts">
            Aurora Population Facts
        </h3>
    


            <h4>What is the current population of Aurora?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Aurora is 389,347.  Aurora, Colorado is the 51st largest city in the US.
            </p>

            
                <h4>What county is Aurora, Colorado in?</h4>
                <p>
                
                    Parts of Aurora are located within
                    Adams County, Arapahoe County and Douglas County.
                    
                </p>
            

            
                
                    <h4>What is the size of Aurora, Colorado in square miles?</h4>
                    Aurora has an area of 
                    154.7 square miles.

                    
                    
                        Aurora is the
                        
                            2nd
                        
                        largest city, by area, in Colorado.
                    
                
            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Aurora?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The current population of Aurora (389,347) is it's peak population.
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Aurora growing?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Aurora has grown
                        40.1% 
                        since the 2000.
                    


                    
                        Aurora, Colorado is growing moderately quickly;
                        it is growing faster than 84%
                        of similarly sized cities since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            
                <h4>Is Aurora the biggest city in Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    No, Aurora is the 3rd largest city in the state of Colorado. The biggest city, <a href="/city/denver-colorado">Denver</a>, is 1.8x bigger than Aurora.
                </p>
            

            
                <h4>What is the population density of Aurora, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                Aurora has a population density of
                2,100.9 people
                per square mile.

                
                
                </p>
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
