        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="demographics">
            Aurora Demographics
        </h3>
    


            
                

                
                <h4>What is the voting age population of Aurora, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Aurora, Colorado, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 233,286.  The voting age population is 48.4% male and 51.6% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Aurora, Colorado residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 11.2% of
                        the residents of Aurora are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Aurora, Colorado?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Aurora are 60.4% White, 16.5% Black, 10.2% Other, 6.5% Asian, 5.2% Two or more races, 0.9% American Indian and 0.4% Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander. Additionally, 28.6% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Aurora, Colorado residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Aurora, 10.7% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 15.0%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    7.9% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Aurora.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Aurora, Colorado residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 71.9% of
                    Aurora residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Aurora, Colorado residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    87.7% of
                    Aurora residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 29.7%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 9.8%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Aurora, Colorado residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Aurora residents aged 5 and older, 33.0% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                21.3% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                3.6% speak an Indo-European language, and
                4.6% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="labor">
            Aurora Income &amp; Labor Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Aurora, Colorado?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Aurora is 4.6%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Aurora, Colorado residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Aurora, 11.2% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Aurora, Colorado?</h4>
                    <p>The median household income in Aurora is $65,100.</p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="housing">
            Aurora Housing &amp; Rent Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are owner-occupied in Aurora, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Aurora, 59.9% of housing units
                    are occupied by their owners.
                </p>
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are rented in Aurora, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    Renters occupy 40.1% of housing units in
                    Aurora.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Aurora, Colorado housing units were built before 1940?</h4>
                    <p>
                        Of all the housing units in Aurora,
                        0.8% of them were build before 1940.
                    </p>
                

                
                

                
                    <h4>What percentage of Aurora, Colorado housing units were built after 2000?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Aurora, 21.6% of the 
                    total housing units were built
                    
                        after the year 2000, which is approximately 
                        
                            29,300 units.
                        
                    
                    </p>
                
                
                
                
                <h4>What is the median monthly rent in Aurora, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    The median gross monthly rent payment for renters in Aurora is
                    $1,328.
                </p>

                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of households in Aurora, Colorado have broadband internet?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Aurora, 87.3% of households have
                    an active broadband internet connection.
                </p>
                
                
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
